This paper deals with image synthesis using deep learning techniques, specifically the CycleGAN model. The focus is on medical imaging, which is a common application area for computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of gradient consistency loss, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning for image processing (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which is a broad area of computer science that includes deep learning (cs.AI). The paper deals with cross-modality image synthesis, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning for medical imaging, which is a subfield of neural engineering (cs.NE).
